review_blob: Hazy pale, small head. Nice hop aroma. Light hop bitterness, not long finish. Thin texture, soft carbonation.
Sweet malt aroma. Clear amber, small short head. Caramel sweet, a little bitterness in the finish. Flat carbonation, thin texture.
Cloudy amber color, medium and long head. A bit weak malty aroma. Medium sweet and bitter, obvious yeast notes. Soft carbonation, creamy texture.
UPDATED: APR 27, 2016
Clear pale to amber color, medium and long head. Light malt aroma. Medium candy sweet and light bitter. Soft carbonation.
Nice fruity aroma with some tropical fruits notes. Amber to red color, medium but short head. Medium bitter, underneath some obvious sweetness.
Hazy pale to orange, medium head. Nice hop aroma with some pine notes. Strong and long-lasting bitterness. Soft carbonation, medium body.
Hazy, very pale color, very little head. Light fruity aroma. Light sweet, some malt notes, a litter sourish finish. Light body.
Very little head, cloudy pale color. Strong fruity aroma with citrus notes. Orange sweet and malt taste. Nice beer when thirsty.
Thick off-white head but short, clear yellow to amber color. Hop and malt aroma. Medium bitter and light sweet. Average carbonation, medium body.
Clear brown color, very small head. Sweet malt aroma and some herb notes. Caramel sweet taste, no obvious bitterness. Medium body, average carbonation.
Clear pale head, almost no head. Some grain aroma. Light bitterness. Average carbonation.
Hazy amber-red color, big white head. Strong hop aroma. Medium sweet and bitter, with yeast notes. Light bitterness in the aftertaste. Lively carbonation.
Small head, hazy yellow. Light aroma with some orange notes. Pleasant sweetness, a bit like orange juice. Soft carbonation. Not much beer characteristics. Some food additive ingredients!!!

Medium white head, clear pale color. Malt and fruity aroma. Sweet and yeast taste, well hidden bitterness, a little sourish at the finish. Medium to high body, a bit sticky texture, average carbonation.
First smells like a wheat beer, then some herb notes. Clear gold, almost no head. Light sweet and a little sourish. Light to medium body, average carbonation, a little dry finish.
Classical wheat beer aroma and taste. Clear pale color, small head. Lively carbonation, not light body.
No obvious aroma. Clear pale, white small to medium head. A little sweet and sourish, no bitterness. Average carbonation.
Nice wheat beer aroma. Hazy pale to gold color, short head. Light sweet and a little fruit sourish. Lively carbonation. A bit abrupt finish.
Moderate hop aroma. Big head, muddy color. Bitter, no obvious sweetness . Light body, thin texture.
Moderate roasted malt aroma. Black with medium tan head. Obvious bitterness lasts long. Creamy texture, medium to full body.
Sweet aroma. Clear amber, poor head. Caramel sweet with some roastiness taste. Very like bock beer.
Average malt aroma. Small off-white head, clear dark brown color. Syrup and caramel sweetness, well hiden bitterness comes out a bit in the aftertaste. Soft to medium carbonation.
Caramel, coriander aroma, not strong. Medium off-white head, hazy dark brown color. Strong taste, sweet, spicy, with some dark fruit flavor. Medium to high body.
aroma is fruity, citrus. Hazy gold, small and short head. Tastes light sweet, a little citrus sourish. Thin body, soft carbonation. A nice beer for refreshing.
Light malt aroma. Moderate off-white head, clear dark ruby color. Medium sweet, almost unnoticeable bitternessh, yeast taste at the finish. Medium body, soft carbonation. Not very distinctive.
Faint wheat beer aroma. Cloudy golden color, small and short head. Not much sweetness, sourish. Thin body, average carbonation.
Obvious malt and citrus aroma, a hint of celery. Hazy amber color. Lightly and not enough wheat sweetness, a little citrus sour. Lively carbonation.
Fruity wheat malt aroma but not strong. Smaller head but darker color than average wheat beers. Malt sweet. Carbonation and body are at a higher level than average wheat beers. Nice beer.
Some malt and and a little ripe fruit aroma. Dark brown, medium long tan head. Taste is complex, with spices, herbs, roasted bitterness, low sweetness. Creamy texture, a bit thin.
A little hop aroma. Clear gold, medium head. Sweet, with a touch of bitterness but diminish quickly. Low carbonation. Thin body.
A little dark fruit or toffee aroma. Small head, cloudy amber color. Taste is candy sweet, combined with low bitterness, with a yeasty finish. Medium body, smooth texture.
A little malt aroma. Clear amber to brown color, small and short head. Taste is a little roasted bitterness, balanced with hints of sweetness.
A little malt aroma. Fair head, pale gold color. Light sweetness and bitterness, high carbonation.
Fair malt, dark fruit, spice aroma. Ruby color and medium off-white head. Caramel sweet, dry fruit taste, with a hint of unnoticeable bitterness.
Sour aroma and some wine hints. Red to brown color, medium tan head. Taste is sour.
Malty and yeast aroma. Big head, cloudy blond to amber color. Creamy texture. Malt sweet and well balanced bitter.
Malty aroma. Clear amber color, small head. Syrup sweet and lively carbonation.
Sweet and fruity aroma, similar to wheat beer. Poor head, clear gold color. Low carbonation. Medium sweet and bitterness.
Typical wheat beer aroma and appearance. The first touch is a bit thin. Wheat sweetness. Nice beer for after sports drinking.
Sweet malt aroma. Small head, clear amber color. Sweet taste, with little bitterness. Not enough carbonation, and thin body.
A little hop aroma. Big white head. Hazy pale to gold color. Taste is somewhat complex. Sweet, not too much bitterness. Yeast and a little bitter aftertaste. Medium to high body. Good beer!
Aroma is a bit weak. Kind of lack the wheat sweet taste. Not very smooth. A bit thin finish. Not a typical hefeweizen.
UPDATED: APR 27, 2016
Fruity and malty aroma. Long white head. Hazy amber color. Combined sweetness and bitterness. Bitter aftertaste.
Hoppy aroma. A small but nice milky chocolate head. Dark brown color. The head feels like a cappuccino head. A little chocolate-like sweetness cover by combined hop and roasted bitterness,
Toffee/caramel aroma but a bit weak. Poor tan head, brown chocolate color. Obvious chocolate taste mixed with roasted bitterness.
beer_name: Cinema Brewers Bock to the Future

review_blob: Very fruity aroma. Nice white head, hazy gold to orange color. Taste is fruit sweet with a little bitterness. Dry finish and bitter aftertaste.
Strong fruity aroma. Nice white and fine head. Hazy pale color. Nice wheat sweet. Great wheat beer!
Hoppy aroma. Clear gold to amber color, short-lasting head. Tastes medium bitter. An average IPA.
